right, and your the pro at it right???

[/quote]

Dankess is a very good scar scripter, have you seen his scripts?[/quote]

Actually i have been a SRL Developer since revision 80something, I was in the first 20 members of the dev crew and i know SRL back and forwards, I have written about 50 scripts for SRL
some of which were availble to the SRL Developers only and the rest were posted on the forums. If you don’t have the pick equiped it won’t find it sorry, you can set Equippick=False in SRL/SRL/SKILL/MINING.SCAr but it doesnt work as good as the version of findpick that fawki modifyed. Also SRL Is designed to work as a AutoResponder if your skilled enough to make it work as the SRL Developer’s have shown on our Forums so no SRL Does not Require your chat to be off you just need to set the Player[].Nick for it to work. What i said earler may not have been as nice as this post but i don’t really care i’m not a nice person, i’m not here to make friends, I simply am a good scripter and have been helping create this include for along time. Please read the manual and learn how it works before giving false information is all i said earler.

PS : To Answer your Question, Yes I Am a Pro at this (h)! lmfao

-Dankness
SRL Admin

and whenever you do the antirandoms then you should have the talking off orelse it will move its mouse acroos the text and that very detectable

This is why your mouse follows any yellow text on the screen please read below and you will learn something… This is quoted directly from the SRL Manual. Please don’t act like a Ass when you don’t have a clue what your talking about i simply corrected your misconsepetions so Everybody will learn how to properly use the include.

For proper detection of Randoms you need to set the Players.Nick!!!!!!!!

Refer to manual if anything is unclear.
Posted at: May 23, 2006, 08:34:25 pmEDIT: About Players.Nick:

SRL checks for randoms by scanning the yellow text from the mainscreen. If you encounter a Random, your name always appears on the mainscreen. That is what we scan for in Nick. Nick doesnt need your whole name. Take two, three or four letters from it and put it in Nick. Example: if your runescape name is Qwertyuiop, good Nicks would be: tyu, erty, uio or iop. Note however that nick should NOT contain the First Letter Of Your RuneScapeName, Since These Are Always capitalised.

item.dc:creator: @Dankness Dankness
item.description:
@Dankness wrote:

You need to Find the pickax head colors before you can call FindHead, please read the SRL manual included with Offical SRL Include downloads to find more information on how to call it, Also i suggest removing all MoveMouseSmoothEx and ClickMouse as they are both highly detectable and SRL has to very good undetectable mouse movements commands that are quite easy to use. Simply use

function MMouse(X, Y, RandX, RandY: integer); By: BenLand100/Mutant Squirrle Description: Moves the mouse along a spline to (X, Y) with an ending randomness of RandX and RandY (If BenMouse=True (Default)) Global var BenMouse determines the behaviour of MMouse.

or

procedure Mouse(mousex, mousey, ranx, rany: Integer; left: Boolean); By: Mutant Squirrle Description: Moves then clicks mouse.

Those are both Directly Out of the SRL Manual.
You Also need to Set BenMouse to True and set MouseSpeed to about 25… All of this information is easyly found in the SRL Include Manual and i belive you can search it will the Control-F command.

Also Without Using the PlayerArray or most importantly Player[0].Nick your AntiRandoms will never work and they will always think there is a random near as that is how it finds the randoms for your charactor unlike many other includes that simply See a Random and Talk to it. WT-Fawki has talked in great detail about how to SetUp the player array in the first section of the manual so it is easy information to obtain.

OFFTopic : If you tryed to use Proper Grammer and Atleast attempted at Spelling most words properly ( IE Includeing atleast 90% of the letters in the words ) then more people would be happy to help you. I for one could barely understand what you even where talking about, Im not saying you have to Know how to spell every single word just atleast Attempt spelling them properly.

-Dankness
SRL Admin

@Cheesehunk wrote:

You don’t need to add the part:

{.include SRL/SRL/Core/AntiRandoms.scar}

It is already automaticially included…

By the way, you do not need such big BITmaps, 29 by 2 works for me on the CLickHereToPlay; part, and you should only need one.

Also, SRL comes with a login function.

LoginPlayer;

Yoru main loop should look like this:

begin SetupSRL; SetupSRLWoodcutting; loadbitmaps; repeat anti_randoms; cut; droplog; until (false); end.

there ya go!
